{"cursor":"11600","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Taxobox\n| image = Actinomycetes_sp_01.png image_width = 240px image_caption = Nocardia\n| asteroides (yellow colonies). regnum = Bacteria phylum = Actinobacteria\n| classis = Actinobacteria ordo = Actinomycetales subordo = Corynebacterineae\n| familia = Nocardiaceae genus = 'Nocardia' genus_authority = Trevisan 1889\n| subdivision_ranks = Species subdivision =\n[[Nocardia aerocolonigenes|N. aerocolonigenes]] [[Nocardia africana|N.\nafricana]] [[Nocardia argentinensis|N. argentinensis]] [[Nocardia\nasteroides|N. asteroides]] [[Nocardia blackwellii|N. blackwellii]]\n[[Nocardia brasiliensis|N. brasiliensis]] [[Nocardia brevicatena|N.\nbrevicatena]] [[Nocardia carnea|N. carnea]] [[Nocardia caviae|N.\ncaviae]] [[Nocardia cerradoensis|N. cerradoensis]] [[Nocardia\ncorallina|N. corallina]] [[Nocardia cyriacigeorgica|N. cyriacigeorgica]]\n[[Nocardia dassonvillei|N. dassonvillei]] [[Nocardia elegans|N.\nelegans]] [[Nocardia farcinica|N. farcinica]] [[Nocardia nigiitansis|N.\nnigiitansis]] [[Nocardia nova|N. nova]] [[Nocardia opaca|N. opaca]]\n[[Nocardia otitidis-cavarium|N. otitidis-cavarium]] [[Nocardia\npaucivorans|N. paucivorans]] [[Nocardia pseudobrasiliensis|N.\npseudobrasiliensis]] [[Nocardia rubra|N. rubra]] [[Nocardia seriolae|N.\nseriolae]] [[Nocardia transvelencesis|N. transvelencesis]] [[Nocardia\nuniformis|N. uniformis]] [[Nocardia vaccinii|N. vaccinii]] [[Nocardia\nveterana|N. veterana]]}}\n\n'Nocardia' is a genus of weakly staining Gram-positive, catalase-positive, rod-\nshaped bacteria. It forms partially acid-fast beaded branching filaments (acting\nas fungi, but being truly bacteria). It has a total of 85 species. Some species\nare non-pathogenic while others are responsible for nocardiosis. Nocardia are found worldwide in soil that is rich with\norganic matter. In addition, Nocardia are oral microflora found in healthy\ngingiva as well as periodontal pockets. Most Nocardia infections ar